# LIMSOC 2026-27 SME-Group Process

**Where the process sits (as at 2026-06-09).** Four informal SME groups are being stood up to give input on the major LIMSOC 2026-27 projects, sitting deliberately outside the formal governance structure (input only, decisions stay where they are now). The EOI email has been drafted, sent to Alex Walton and David Potter for review last week, and Alex has replied with stakeholder coverage per group plus a clear "go via the area leads" steer rather than broadcasting. Nick Giblin (SEMO, the channel for SDO/SAC/ARO reps across three of the four groups) hasn't been returning calls; engagement with him is now happening via a written email rather than further phone attempts. Target is to ship the EOI to nominated reps Monday 15 June so the SME work can support project kick-offs from 1 July.

**Why.** This is the engagement model for the SLCO volunteer role's biggest 2026-27 commitment — getting more people involved on the LIMSOC priorities without overloading the small core team. The lead-channel approach (vs broadcast) is Alex's call and Nick has accepted it: rep support tends to equal leadership support, which keeps the SME work aligned with the broader strategy. Two operational constraints are live: (a) the Operations Officer role is unfilled until the August AGM, with Sarah Seddon as incoming appointee — affects two of the four groups; (b) the Club Captain rep nomination channel for the Rostering group is still open. The work is bound to a hard date (1 July project kick-offs) — slipping the EOI past this week starts costing season runway.

